import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='pressure', data=data, ax=ax, label='Pressure')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temperature', data=data, ax=ax, label='Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of pressure and temperature over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = pd.to_datetime(data['hour'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.hour
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='hour', y='pressure', data=data, ax=ax, color='blue')
    sns.boxplot(x='hour', y='temperature', data=data, ax=ax, color='red')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of pressure and temperature by hour of the day?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(labels=['Pressure', 'Temperature'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['month'] = pd.to_datetime(data['month'], format='%m').dt.month_name().str.slice(stop=3)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='month', y='wind', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['wind'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind by month?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce').dt.year
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='temperature', hue='year', kde=True, multiple='stack', palette='viridis')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['temperature'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature by year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
